✨Creamy Chia Pudding With @kaysnaturals Cookie Bites✨⁣
⁣
I've really been loving chia pudding lately, especially because I love making mine extra thick and creamy by making it with coconut cream🤤 I also made this one extra delicious and protein packed by adding @kaysnaturals cookie bites. They have 12 grams of protein per serving and they are so delicious, crunchy, and cinnamon-ey! You can use code "veggieworld" to get 30% off these yummy cookie bites, or any other products from @kaysnaturals by shopping on their website🤗⁣
⁣
🤍Creamy Chia Pudding🤍⁣
⁣
Ingredients⁣
1 can coconut milk⁣
1/2 cup chia seeds⁣
2 tbsp maple syrup⁣
1/2 tsp vanilla⁣
@kaysnaturals cookie bites⁣
⁣
Directions⁣
To a bowl, add the coconut milk, chia seeds, maple syrup, and vanilla. Stir all of the ingredients well. Cover the bowl with a lid and place in the fridge overnight. Your chia pudding will be thick, creamy, and ready to enjoy in the morning. Add it to a bowl and top with your cookie bites and some berries😋🍓⁣
⁣

Breaking my 3 day fast with this beautiful and delicious meal. Yeah you read that right. 3 days! The last thing I ate was a bite of sausage on Monday morning. 
•
I intermittently fast most of the time. I don’t usually have my first meal until around noon and my last meal is usually around 6-7. This is easy. 
•
Every once in a while I will do a 24 hour fast. That was the plan this time. But for some reason after the first day I said to myself “let’s see if we can do 2 days”. I felt pretty good after 2 and said “let’s do 3”.
•
In all honesty it was a lot easier than I expected. The worst part was being around food and choosing not to eat it. I didn’t feel bad. I still had plenty of energy and my mood was great. I was starting to feel some effects last night. But nothing major. 
•
With all that being said I’m not some crazy person. I’ve done some research on this. There are some great benefits to doing this. It is great at detoxing your body. It really helps your immune system. Not to mention the mental strength it requires to do this on purpose. 
•
I’m not advocating that everyone do this. There are plenty of people that should not do this. But if you know what you’re doing and you listen to your body you can accomplish great things. 
•
•
•

Make Ahead Chicken Breakfast Sausage! #breakfast #breakfastsausage #chicken  VEGAN twist, can be replaced with vegan textured protein. @beyondmeat  454 grams Extra Lean Ground Chicken
1/4 cup Parsley (very finely chopped)
3 Garlic (cloves, minced)
1/4 tsp Sea Salt
1 tbsp Avocado Oil.  In a mixing bowl combine the chicken, parsley, garlic, and salt. Mix well.
Heat the oil in a non-stick pan over medium heat.
Form the mixture into thin patties approximately four inches (10-centimeters) in diameter. In batches, cook for four to five minutes per side or until cooked through. Serve and enjoy!

❄️ 😴 It's winter. An for many of us, retaining a big yawn in chilly weather is almost a feat! ⁠
⁠
❄️☃️ In this cold weather, even dogs yawn! ⁠
⁠
But don't feel guilty, because Science says that far from being a mark of boredom or fatigue, yawning might help your brain cool off. Literally.⁠
⁠
✔️A study led by Andrew Gallup showed that yawning frequency varies with the season and that people are less likely to yawn when the heat outdoors exceeds body temperature. In a few words, yawning can serve as a method for regulating brain temperature.⁠
✔️The scientists found that participants were more likely to yawn in the winter than in the summer when ambient temperatures were equal to or exceeding body temperature. They concluded that warmer temperatures provide no relief for overheated brains, which, according to the thermoregulatory theory of yawning, stay cool via a heat exchange with the air drawn in during a yawn.⁠
⁠
😄 So keep calm, and yawn in peace! 😁⁠
⁠
📸: Linda Kazares on Unsplash. ⁠
⁠Source: https://www.princeton.edu/news/2011/09/19/more-sign-sleepiness-yawning-may-cool-brain⁠

Mornings in our house can be chaos.

Everyone sitting around the table, quietly waking up for the morning, giggling, smiling and talking about what they hope will happen during the day. 

Nothing puts a smile on my kids’ faces in the mornings quite like chocolate chip muffins. 
But shhh. There’s a secret. 
There’s veggies in these muffins. 

@veggiesmadegreat Banana Chocolate Chip Muffins are made with Gluten Free Oats, Semi Sweet Chocolate Chips, Brown Rice Flour, Cane Sugar and Zuchinni.

Eat balanced breakfast!

If there is anything worse than being stressed, it’s being stressed AND hungry! To prevent you from getting hangry hours before lunch, we’re going to show you how to build a balanced breakfast.

The key things you want to focus on for breakfast are: protein, carbs, fat, fiber, and some color from fruits or veggies. Nut butters (are you team almond butter or PB??) provide protein and healthy fats, oats and other whole grains give you carbs and fiber, and eggs and yogurt are good sources of protein. Here are some of our favorite breakfast combos:

- Whole wheat toast or @vansfood waffles topped with nut butter (@sunbutter or @crazyrichardspb) and a side of fruit 
- @siggisdairy yogurt with granola (@purely_elizabeth or @kindsnacks), fruit, and nut butter 
- Overnight oats topped with fruit and nuts 
- Scrambled eggs (try @justegg101 for a delicious plant-based egg option!) with potatoes and veggies

•Berries & Cream Yogurt•
This is my go to Saturday morning breakfast. Saturday’s are a busy day for me at the gym, so I need a meal that is going to fill me up and fuel my body. 
...
Ingredients:
•1/2 cup quick oats 
•1 cup water (you could use milk too!)
•2 tsps peanut butter 
•1/2 tsp cinnamon 
•20g vanilla protein powder (I used @1stphorm Level 1) 
•170g nonfat greek yogurt 
•1/2 cup berries of your choice (I used blackberries and raspberries) 
•1/2 tbsp honey for drizzling 
....
1. Prepare the oatmeal on the stove or microwave (oats, water, cinnamon & pb). I like to add in the pb while it’s cooking to help thicken up the oatmeal. 
2. Once cooked, stir in the protein powder
3. Top oatmeal with yogurt 
4. Add on berries and drizzle some honey over the top! 
...
You can easily adjust the amount of oats for higher carbs, or add addition protein powder or yogurt for more protein. 
My macros for this meal were: 
30P/10F/55C 
I am eating this before a workout so I want to keep my protein and carbs high but my fat low! 
Try this out next time you need a pre-workout breakfast! 💪
